<subSubSection id="C326E0F8A64F221538EB3F7B0F172A1C" pageId="10" pageNumber="93" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8B83B373A64F221538EB3F7B0A982B13" blockId="10.[189,416,1035,1062]" box="[189,416,1035,1062]" pageId="10" pageNumber="93">
<emphasis id="B9486F61A64F221538EB3F7B0A0E2B10" bold="true" box="[189,310,1035,1061]" pageId="10" pageNumber="93">Diagnosis</emphasis>
(female)
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B83B373A64F221538EB3F4A0F172A1C" blockId="10.[188,1399,1082,1321]" pageId="10" pageNumber="93">
Body length 3.00– 
<quantity id="4CC41E96A64F221539CE3F4A093C2B60" box="[408,516,1082,1109]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.3" pageId="10" pageNumber="93" unit="mm" value="3.3">3.30 mm</quantity>
; antenna as long as or slightly longer than body, F15 length 2.0 × its width (
<figureCitation id="1307AFF6A64F221538903F2D0A1B2B4D" box="[198,291,1117,1144]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="11.[189,232,1963,1989]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,750,1924]" captionTargetId="figure-178@11.[189,1398,750,1924]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Fig. 4. Microplitis docilis Nixon, 1970, ♀, TMUC-HBMMP0013. A. Habitus, lateral view B. Head, dorsal view. C. Mesosoma, dorsal view. D. Fore wing. E. Hind wing. F. Metasoma, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4690338" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4690338/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="93">Fig. 4A</figureCitation>
); anteromesoscutum and mesoscutellar disc rugose; notauli slightly defined with coarse rugosity (
<figureCitation id="1307AFF6A64F221538903FF10A1D2BAE" box="[198,293,1153,1179]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="11.[189,232,1963,1989]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,750,1924]" captionTargetId="figure-178@11.[189,1398,750,1924]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Fig. 4. Microplitis docilis Nixon, 1970, ♀, TMUC-HBMMP0013. A. Habitus, lateral view B. Head, dorsal view. C. Mesosoma, dorsal view. D. Fore wing. E. Hind wing. F. Metasoma, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4690338" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4690338/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="93">Fig. 4C</figureCitation>
); vein R1 shorter than pterostigma (i.e., vein R1 longer than pterostigma half); 1 
<superScript id="7C491E3BA64F22153CBC3FF10FCD2BBA" attach="left" box="[1258,1269,1153,1167]" fontSize="6" pageId="10" pageNumber="93">st</superScript>
discal cell length 1.1–1.2 × its width, vein 1CUb 2.0–2.6 × as long as vein 1CUa (
<figureCitation id="1307AFF6A64F22153BAC3FD40F612B8B" box="[1018,1113,1188,1214]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="11.[189,232,1963,1989]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,750,1924]" captionTargetId="figure-178@11.[189,1398,750,1924]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Fig. 4. Microplitis docilis Nixon, 1970, ♀, TMUC-HBMMP0013. A. Habitus, lateral view B. Head, dorsal view. C. Mesosoma, dorsal view. D. Fore wing. E. Hind wing. F. Metasoma, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4690338" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4690338/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="93">Fig. 4D</figureCitation>
); T1 length 1.5–1.6 × its maximum width, more or less broadening posteriorly, T1 coarsely rugose (
<figureCitation id="1307AFF6A64F22153C763FB80F422BD7" box="[1056,1146,1224,1250]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="11.[189,232,1963,1989]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,750,1924]" captionTargetId="figure-178@11.[189,1398,750,1924]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Fig. 4. Microplitis docilis Nixon, 1970, ♀, TMUC-HBMMP0013. A. Habitus, lateral view B. Head, dorsal view. C. Mesosoma, dorsal view. D. Fore wing. E. Hind wing. F. Metasoma, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4690338" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4690338/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="93">Fig. 4F</figureCitation>
). Colour: body black; antennal flagellum brown; scape yellow; pterostigma black or dark brown; legs yellow or reddish yellow (except for black coxae and brown or reddish brown metafemur) (
<figureCitation id="1307AFF6A64F22153B953E7E0F1A2A1C" box="[963,1058,1294,1321]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="11.[189,232,1963,1989]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,750,1924]" captionTargetId="figure-178@11.[189,1398,750,1924]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Fig. 4. Microplitis docilis Nixon, 1970, ♀, TMUC-HBMMP0013. A. Habitus, lateral view B. Head, dorsal view. C. Mesosoma, dorsal view. D. Fore wing. E. Hind wing. F. Metasoma, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4690338" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4690338/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="93">Fig. 4A</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
